					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In a way it would be realistic for the purpose of golf/minigolf: If you don't control your breathing, your swing will risk being off. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" /> <br /><br />A ribbon controller could actually be a relatively interesting peripheral. More easily precise than a theremin, but unlike a potentiometer (arkanoid controller), you can make direct jumps with your fingers. The slew rate would be controllable in software rather than capped by the inertia/travel of the pot. You could layer it with a pressure sensor. But what sort of game would benefit from it? My first thought is some sort of player-controlled-scrolling sniper game.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
